.TH "dma_resv_reserve_shared" 9 "dma_resv_reserve_shared" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_resv_reserve_shared \- Reserve space to add shared fences to a dma_resv.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dma_resv_reserve_shared
.BI "(struct dma_resv *obj "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_fences "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "obj" 12
reservation object
.IP "num_fences" 12
number of fences we want to add
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Should be called before \fBdma_resv_add_shared_fence\fP.  Must
be called with obj->lock held.

RETURNS
Zero for success, or -errno
